T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Purpose and Scope of Risk Management Activities) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This plan defines the product-specific risk management activities for SmartShift Planner) Tj
T*
(across design, development, verification, release, operation, and post-release monitoring.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Scope includes:) Tj
T*
(- software failure, cybersecurity, privacy, and AI/ML risks) Tj
T*
(- supplier and integration risks for identity and Microsoft Graph calendar sync) Tj
T*
(- production and post-production feedback relevant to harm prevention and compliance) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Product Description) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SmartShift Planner is a multi-tenant web application that creates and publishes work) Tj
T*
(schedules. It uses AI-assisted ranking to propose schedules and a human approval step before) Tj
T*
(publishing to employee calendars.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Responsibilities and Authorities) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Risk Manager: maintains the risk file and chairs formal reviews.) Tj
T*
(- Engineering Lead: ensures technical mitigations are implemented and verified.) Tj
T*
(- Security Engineer: owns threat modeling, vulnerability treatment, and hardening evidence.) Tj
T*
(- Privacy Officer: confirms lawful processing, minimization, retention, and breach) Tj
T*
(readiness.) Tj
T*
(- Product Owner: confirms acceptable residual business risk and intended use alignment.) Tj
T*
(- Quality Manager: verifies completeness of evidence and CAPA closure.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Authority to block release is explicitly granted to the Risk Manager, Security Engineer, and) Tj
T*
(Privacy Officer when unacceptable residual risk remains.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. Methods and Procedures) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- preliminary hazard analysis for major workflow changes) Tj
T*
(- FMEA for component and process-level failure analysis) Tj
T*
(- misuse and abuse case analysis for adversarial and insider scenarios) Tj
T*
(- security threat modeling for interfaces, secrets, identity, and tenant boundaries) Tj
T*
(- privacy impact checks for new data uses and exports) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5. Risk Acceptance Criteria) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- No untreated critical security or privacy risk may be accepted for release.) Tj
